topic_metadata.title: Why are there extra arrowheads in the exported pdf?

posts.name: ShabbyGayBar
posts.cooked:
original svg file:

code:

#figure(
  image("pipeline_sar_adc_block_diagram.svg", width: 80%),
  caption: [Pipeline SAR ADC Block Diagram],
) <pipeline_sar_adc_block_diagram>

preview:

图片785×362 21.5 KB

exported pdf:

图片784×410 34.6 KB

Where on earth did those two arrowheads come from?
Was it the svg or typst?

posts.name: SillyFreak
posts.cooked: I downloaded the SVG file from your project and opened it in Inkscape, and these arrows show up, so I assume it’s the SVG. (Edit, would be interesting why the arrowheads don’t show up in Tinymist, and/or if this is particularly unusual SVG code leading to this different treatment)

posts.name: ShabbyGayBar
posts.cooked:
I learned from the Chinese community that the svg might contain HTML Foreign Object format. Hence those object are only visible in certain svg viewers.

typst-doc-cn.github.io

为什么 mermaid/draw.io 生成的 SVG 图片导入后没有文字？ | Typst 中文社区导航

本文档收录了日经问题（QQ 群中经常有人问的问题），以及官方文档和小蓝书中未提到的一些零碎的使用技巧。
posts.raw:
I learned from the Chinese community that the svg might contain `HTML Foreign Object` format. Hence those object are only visible in certain svg viewers.
https://typst-doc-cn.github.io/guide/FAQ/mermaid.html
